# Hospital Revenue Analytics Dashboard 🏥💰

An interactive and data-driven **Power BI Dashboard** engineered to track, analyze, and optimize hospital financial performance. This project provides health administration executives with real-time visibility into revenue streams, billing cycles, department profitability, and outstanding receivables.

---

## 🚀 Key Features

* **Financial Performance Overview:** Real-time tracking of Total Revenue, Net Profit Margins, and Average Cost per Patient.
* **Departmental Revenue Breakdown:** In-depth comparative analysis across critical departments (e.g., Cardiology, ER, Oncology, Outpatient).
* **Payer & Claims Analysis:** Performance evaluation of insurance provider reimbursement rates, claims denial percentages, and self-pay distributions.
* **Operational Efficiency Metrics:** Visualization of how average length of stay (ALOS) correlates directly with billing and total revenue generation.
* **Historical Trend Forecasting:** Time-series tracking of financial collection efficiency to detect seasonal variance in healthcare revenue.

---

## 🛠️ Built With

* **Power BI Desktop:** Core platform utilized for report generation and visual designs.
* **DAX (Data Analysis Expressions):** Advanced customized modeling for calculated measures (e.g., YoY growth, collection rates).
* **Power Query:** Robust ETL processes used for cleaning, merging, and transforming unstructured data sources.

---

## 📂 Repository Structure

* `📁 Dashboard/` - Contains the final `.pbix` Power BI project file.
* `📁 Data/` - Cleaned/synthesized datasets utilized for the model (Excel/CSV formats).
* `📁 Screenshots/` - High-resolution captures of the active workspace tabs.

# Hospital Patient Care & Clinical Insights Dashboard 🩺👥

An advanced **Power BI Dashboard** developed to monitor clinical operations, patient care quality, and hospital capacity management. This business intelligence solution empowers healthcare teams to improve patient outcomes, optimize bed utilization, and manage clinical resources effectively.

---

## 🚀 Key Features

* **Patient Volume & Capacity KPIs:** High-level metrics for Total Admissions, Discharge Rates, and Active Bed Occupancy.
* **Care Quality & Safety Tracking:** Visual insights into patient readmission rates, clinical complication statistics, and satisfaction scores (HCAHPS).
* **Demographic & Diagnostic Profiling:** Detailed breakdowns of patient groups categorized by age tier, gender, and primary illness classification.
* **Operational Bottleneck Discovery:** Length of Stay (LOS) analysis sliced by attending physician and clinical department to reduce wait times.
* **Critical Care Monitoring:** Specialized analysis tracking Intensive Care Unit (ICU) admission rates and corresponding critical care operational metrics.

---

## 🛠️ Built With

* **Power BI Desktop:** The application used for data visualization, dashboard building, and data model mapping.
* **DAX (Data Analysis Expressions):** Complex calculations constructed for active bed counts, moving averages, and patient satisfaction benchmarks.
* **Power Query:** Heavy transformations utilizing relational model structures optimized for clinical data patterns.

---

## 📂 Repository Structure

* `📁 Dashboard/` - Holds the complete `.pbix` data model project.
* `📁 Data/` - Anonymized/sample clinical data sheets feeding the model architecture.
* `📁 Screenshots/` - Interface views highlighting active filters and slicer selections.
